Class WebSocket

java.lang.Object
  WebSocket
All Implemented Interfaces:
WebSocketProtocol
public final class WebSocket
extends java.lang.Object
implements WebSocketProtocol

Represents one end (client or server) of a single WebSocket connection. Takes care of the "handshake" phase, then allows for easy sending of text frames, and recieving frames through an event-based model. This is an inner class, used by WebSocketClient and WebSocketServer, and should never need to be instantiated directly by your code.

Author:
Nathan Rajlich
